# Error handling (Orbit Wars)

Adapted from [cursorrules-collection `practices/error-handling.mdc`](https://github.com/nedcodes-ok/cursorrules-collection/blob/main/rules-mdc/practices/error-handling.mdc).

## Classify failures

- **Operational:** invalid Hydra override, missing checkpoint, Docker validation failed, gate threshold miss — clear messages and non-zero CLI exit.
- **Programmer:** shape mismatch in JAX, wrong `TurnBatch` dims, broken import layer — fix the code; do not mask with broad `except Exception`.

## Python rules

- No bare `except:`; catch specific types (`ValueError`, `FileNotFoundError`, `subprocess.CalledProcessError`).
- Wrap low-level errors at boundaries: tournament subprocess → `RuntimeError` with checkpoint path and job id.
- Never catch-and-ignore; log or re-raise with context.

## Hydra / config

- Validate in `src/config/runtime.py` / schema — fail at compose time with which group/key failed.
- Resolved config is truth: `uv run ow train print_resolved_config=true` when debugging default vs YAML mismatches.

## CLI / agents

- Prefer `ow benchmark gate run <id> --verbose --out /tmp/gate.json` (JSON on stdout) over parsing unstructured logs.
- Do not relax calibrated thresholds in `docs/benchmarks/preflight-calibration.json` to force green gates.
